                                </div>
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">1. Introduction</h2>
                            </div>
                            <div class="prose max-w-none text-gray-600">
                                <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
                                    The <span class="font-semibold text-blue-600">Watt-dBm Conversion Tool</span> is a professional utility designed for RF engineering conversions. This tool allows you to convert power values between <span class="font-medium">Watts (W)</span> and <span class="font-medium">dBm (decibels relative to 1 milliwatt)</span> using CSV data files.
                                </p>
                                <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-blue-50 border border-blue-200">
                                    <p class="text-sm text-blue-800">
                                        <i class="fas fa-bullseye mr-2"></i>
                                        <span class="font-semibold">Purpose:</span> Streamline power unit conversions for RF engineers and network professionals.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Understanding the Units -->
                    <section id="understanding" class="content-section mb-10">
                        <div class="bg-white shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-green-100 flex items-center justify-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-ruler text-green-600"></i>
                                </div>
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">2. Understanding the Units</h2>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-orange-100 p-5 border border-orange-200">
                                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-orange-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold">W</div>
                                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">Watt (W)</h3>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                                        A unit of power in the International System of Units (SI). 
                                        <span class="font-semibold block mt-2">1 Watt = 1 joule per second</span>
                                    </p>
                                    <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 bg-white/60 px-3 py-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-info-circle mr-1"></i>SI derived unit for power
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-purple-100 p-5 border border-purple-200">
                                    <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-3">
                                        <div class="w-8 h-8 bg-purple-500 flex items-center justify-center text-white font-bold text-xs">dBm</div>
                                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">dBm</h3>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                                        A unit of level used to indicate that a power level is expressed in decibels with reference to one milliwatt (mW).
                                    </p>
                                    <div class="mt-3 text-xs text-gray-500 bg-white/60 px-3 py-2">
                                        <i class="fas fa-info-circle mr-1"></i>Relative to 1 mW reference
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </section>

                    <!-- Conversion Formulas -->
                    <section id="formulas" class="content-section mb-10">
                        <div class="bg-white shadow-sm border border-gray-200 p-6">
                            <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-6">
                                <div class="w-10 h-10 bg-purple-100 flex items-center justify-center">
                                    <i class="fas fa-calculator text-purple-600"></i>
                                </div>
                                <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-800">3. Conversion Formulas</h2>
                            </div>
                            
                            <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
                                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-6 border border-blue-200">
                                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-right text-blue-600"></i>
                                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">Watt → dBm</h3>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="bg-white p-4 border border-blue-200 shadow-sm">
                                        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono text-blue-700">
                                            P(dBm) = 10 × log₁₀(P(W) × 1000)
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
                                        Multiply power in Watts by 1000, then take the base-10 logarithm and multiply by 10.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                                
                                <div class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-green-100 p-6 border border-green-200">
                                    <div class="flex items-center gap-2 mb-4">
                                        <i class="fas fa-arrow-left text-green-600"></i>
                                        <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800">dBm → Watt</h3>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="bg-white p-4 border border-green-200 shadow-sm">
                                        <p class="text-center text-lg font-mono text-green-700">
                                            P(W) = 10^(P(dBm)/10) / 1000
                                        </p>
                                    </div>
                                    <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
                                        Divide dBm value by 10, raise 10 to that power, then divide by 1000.
                                    </p>
                                </div>
                            </div>

                            <!-- Quick Reference Table -->
                            <div class="mt-6">
                                <h4 class="font-semibold text-gray-700 mb-3 flex items-center gap-2">
                                    <i class="fas fa-table text-gray-500"></i>
                                    Quick Reference Table
                                </h4>
                                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                                    <table class="w-full text-sm">
                                        <thead>
                                            <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                                                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Power (W)</th>
                                                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Power (dBm)</th>
                                                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Power (W)</th>
                                                <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-700">Power (dBm)</th>
                                            </tr>
                                        </thead>
                                        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
                                            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">0.001 W (1 mW)</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">0 dBm</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">1 W</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">30 dBm</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">0.01 W (10 mW)</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">10 dBm</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">2 W</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">33 dBm</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">0.1 W (100 mW)</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">20 dBm</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">10 W</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">40 dBm</td>
                                            </tr>
                                            <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50">
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">0.5 W (500 mW)</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">27 dBm</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono">100 W</td>
                                                <td class="px-4 py-2 font-mono text-blue-600">50 dBm</td>
                                            </tr>
                                        </tbody>
                                    </table>
                                </div>
                            </div>
